---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const publishedDate = "14 July 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Why I Built FuelSave India | Praveen Builds"
  description="The story behind FuelSave India and the problems Praveen Kumar wanted to solve for vehicle owners."
>
  <article class="article container">
    <a class="back-link" href="/blog">← Back to blog</a>

    <header class="article-header">
      <p class="category">FuelSave India</p>

      <h1>Why I Built FuelSave India</h1>

      <p class="intro">
        FuelSave India began with a simple question: how can an ordinary vehicle
        owner clearly understand where their fuel money is going?
      </p>

      <div class="metadata">
        <span>Praveen Kumar</span>
        <span>{publishedDate}</span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="article-content">
      <h2>The problem I noticed</h2>

      <p>
        Most vehicle owners know the price of fuel and how much they paid at the
        petrol pump, but they do not have a clear picture of their vehicle's
        actual running cost.
      </p>

      <p>
        Important information such as monthly fuel expenditure, average mileage,
        cost per kilometre and changes in vehicle efficiency is often scattered
        across receipts, notes or memory.
      </p>

      <p>
        I wanted to create one simple place where this information could be
        recorded and understood.
      </p>

      <h2>The idea behind FuelSave India</h2>

      <p>
        FuelSave India is a mobile application that helps users record fuel
        refills and understand their vehicle expenses.
      </p>

      <p>The application is designed to help users track:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Fuel quantity and price</li>
        <li>Odometer readings</li>
        <li>Average vehicle mileage</li>
        <li>Monthly and lifetime fuel expenses</li>
        <li>Distance travelled</li>
        <li>Approximate cost per kilometre</li>
        <li>Multiple vehicles</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why I chose to build it myself</h2>

      <p>
        As an Electronics and Communication Engineering student, I have always
        been interested in solving practical problems through technology.
      </p>

      <p>
        Building FuelSave India gave me an opportunity to learn mobile
        application development while working on a product that could provide
        real value.
      </p>

      <p>
        I built the application using Flutter and Dart. I used SQLite for local
        data storage so that users can access their records without depending on
        a continuous internet connection.
      </p>

      <h2>What I learned</h2>

      <p>
        Developing the application taught me that product development involves
        much more than writing code. A useful product also needs clear
        calculations, reliable data handling, a simple interface and an
        understanding of how people will actually use it.
      </p>

      <p>
        I worked through challenges involving mileage calculations, partial
        refills, multiple vehicles, analytics, backup and restore, and responsive
        interface design.
      </p>

      <h2>What comes next</h2>

      <p>
        FuelSave India is still evolving. Future improvements may include
        smarter fuel-entry automation, better insights, vehicle maintenance
        reminders and optional OBD-II integration.
      </p>

      <p>
        Through this blog, I will document the development process, technical
        decisions, mistakes and lessons behind the application. My goal is to
        help other students and builders learn from a real project rather than
        only from theoretical examples.
      </p>

      <div class="closing-box">
        <strong>FuelSave India is more than an application project.</strong>

        <p>
          It is my journey of learning how to identify a problem, build a
          solution and continuously improve it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

